<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bellow" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bellow,</orth> vb., to roar; used of bulls: <bibl n="shak. mv 5.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 28</bibl>. of bulls and lions: <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.311" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 311</bibl>. of men: <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.212" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 212</bibl> <cit><quote>(--ed out). the croaking raven doth b. for revenge,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.265" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 265</bibl></cit>.
